 below $10^{19}$ eV. Furthermore, if these are the sources\nof UHECRs above $10^{19}$ eV, a local magnetic structure surrounding the Milky\nWay is needed to explain the observed isotropy at $\\sim 10^{19}$ eV, which may\nbe incompatible with large magnetic structures around all galaxies for the\nUHECR-induced cascade model to work with reasonable jet powers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Dec 2014 18:46:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 17 Dec 2014 04:03:12 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 9 Dec 2015 14:17:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-22"}
