ance in the outflow is 10$^{-10}$,\nwhich is 10$\\times$ lower than in the envelope and in the outflows of high- and\nlow-mass protostars. Since beam size effects can only increase this estimate by\na factor of 2, we suggest that the water in the outflow is affected by\ndissociating UV radiation due to the low extinction in the outflow lobe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Dec 2014 22:02:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
